%N A392127 The smallest k >= 0 that can be represented as a linear combination of 1^2, 2^2, ..., n^2 with coefficients +-1 and that cannot be represented using 1^2, 2^2, ..., m^2 with 1<=m<n.
%C A392127 a(n) is the smallest k >= 0 such that A231015(k) = n.
%H A392127 Alois P. Heinz, <a href="/A392127/b392127.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..145</a>
%e A392127 a(1) = 1: 1^2 = 1.
%e A392127 a(2) = 3: -1^2 + 2^2 = 3.
%e A392127 a(7) = 0: 1^2 + 2^2 - 3^2 + 4^2 - 5^2 - 6^2 + 7^2 = 0.
%p A392127 b:= proc(n, i) option remember; (m-> n<=m and (n=m or
%p A392127       b(abs(n-i^2), i-1) or b(n+i^2, i-1)))(i*(i+1)*(2*i+1)/6)
%p A392127     end:
%p A392127 g:= proc(n) option remember; local k; for k while not b(n, k) do od; k end:
%p A392127 a:= proc(n) option remember; local k; for k from 0 while not g(k)=n do od; k end:
%p A392127 seq(a(n), n=1..47);
